<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I&#39;ve been playing with plantuml src in org files to generate drawings. It works great except for one thing, the indentation gets lost when I add nested objects.</p> <p>Where should I look to extend the existing indentation code to handle nested cases?</p> <pre><code>Minor modes enabled in this buffer: Display-Line-Numbers Font-Lock Org-Src Visual-Line The major mode is plantuml mode defined in plantuml-mode.el: </code></pre> <p>Should I be looking at the plantuml major mode first, or the Org-src minor mode to noodle with the indents?</p> <p>Any recommendations on how to approach indentation config?</p> <p>Example showing how the indents get lost:</p> <pre><code>* Components Drawing #+begin_src plantuml :file ComponentDiagram.svg @startuml Component Diagram &#39; Components component ExternaComponent1 package &quot;Subsystem&quot; { component SubSysComp1 [ Subsystem Component 1 ] package &quot;InternalNestedSubsystem&quot; { package &quot;InternalDoubleNestedSubsystem&quot; { component SubSubComp1 [ Sub-Subsystem Component 1 ] component SubSubComp2 [ Sub-Subsystem Component 2 ] SubSubComp1 -() internalInterface1 internalInterface1 )- SubSubComp2 } &#39; This lines up correctly } &#39; This should be one indent to the left } &#39; This should be all the way to the left @enduml &#39; This should be all the way to the left instead of indented. #+end_src </code></pre> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/HappyDancingApe"> /u/HappyDancingApe </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w15459/indentation_question_org_plantuml/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w15459/indentation_question_org_plantuml/">[comments]</a></span>